newsitem.title: USA: CBOT soy products end mostly lower as soy slides.
newsitem.headline: CBOT soy products end mostly lower as soy slides.

text.p: CBOT soy product futures closed mostly lower on a slide in soybean futures, traders said.
Profit taking on the meal/oil spread also was noted but trading was quiet compared with recent sessions, they said.
Soymeal futures volume was estimated at 19,000, down from 24,559 Thursday, according to the CBOT. Soymeal options volume was estimated at 1,900, down from 2,127 contracts Thursday.
Soyoil futures volume was estimated at 16,000, down from 17,786 contracts Thursday. Soyoil options volume was estimated at 600, down from 803 Thursday.
Soymeal futures closed $1.60 per ton lower to $2.50 per ton higher, with September down $1.00 at $258.10. Soyoil closed 0.01 to 0.10 cent per lb lower, with September down 0.09 at 24.90.
